A man was left injured in a collision involving three vehicles in Shongweni on Wednesday morning.
ER24 spokesperson Russel Meiring said in a statement that the victim, believed to be in his 30s, had been left seriously injured following the collision on the N3 Key Ridge.ADVERTISINGinRead invented by Teads
"Paramedics arrived on the scene to find that three vehicles had collided and were found on the side of the road. A man, believed to be in his 30s, was found lying in the centre median."
They assessed the man and found that he had sustained numerous injuries, leaving him in a serious condition.
"The man was treated for his injuries and was provided with advanced life support interventions. Once treated, the man was transported to Hillcrest Hospital for further treatment."
Meiring said it was believed that the man had lost control of his vehicle, causing it to crash into the centre median. He then attempted to flag down and slow other vehicles when he was hit.
Local authorities were on the scene for further investigations.
